Minister in the Presidency Jackson Mthembu. JOHANNESBURG - Late Minister in the Presidency, Jackson Mthembu will be honoured with an official state funeral at his home in Emalahleni, Mpumalanga on Sunday. Mthembu died on Thursday from COVID-related complications. READ:Â Jackson Mthembu remembered by his colleagues The national flag will fly at half-mast from Saturday morning, 23 January until Sunday evening, 24 January, the day on which Mthembu will be laid to rest. A memorial service will be held on Saturday at the GCIS Auditorium in Hatfield, Tshwane.